      "writtenOn": "2020-03-06T23:06:26Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The \"Docker cache\" is really just another name for the \"work\" cache. The tasks using CACHES_DOCKER probably should have instead just used different subdirs of the work cache, but Kevin was being careful when he first added Docker builds and decided to put it in a completely separate cache.\n\nTasks that don\u0027t need to compile or are using the work cache don\u0027t need the \"Docker cache\".",
      "revId": "2d639c8804e1c0104a8cd51b86a9bea63f434ff0",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1f048798_9bcabbc5",
        "filename": "infra/bots/gen_tasks_logic/task_builder.go",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 227,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-03-09T12:38:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m a little confused by this; anything built in a docker container (at least by default) ends up owned by root, so we absolutely should be using a separate cache for these tasks to avoid poisoning the work cache. We have an open bug which is caused by this: https://bugs.chromium.org/p/skia/issues/detail?id\u003d9749\n\nChanged the logic to reflect your comment, removed the variable so that it doesn\u0027t accidentally get used elsewhere, and added a comment to clarify.\n\nIdeally these \"uses\" functions would have minimal logic; they should really be \"all tasks which use X need these caches/dimensions/dependencies/whatever\"",
      "parentUuid": "970b7af5_6f54ae58",
      "revId": "2d639c8804e1c0104a8cd51b86a9bea63f434ff0",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
